  "prompt": "Are you even really dating someone if you see them once per week for just a few hours?",
  "response": "That depends on individual circumstances, communication, and relationship goals. Some couples have limited time together due to:\n- Long distance relationships\n- Busy work/school schedules\n- Different living situations\n\nWhat matters most is:\n- Quality of time spent together\n- Emotional connection\n- Clear communication about expectations\n- Mutual commitment\n\nIf both people feel satisfied and connected despite limited time, it can still be a meaningful relationship. However, if one person feels unfulfilled, it might be worth discussing.",
